<TITLE> T20 fever starts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, April 30 (bdnews24.com) - The proceedings of the third ICC T20 World Cup is going to start in West Indies from today, 30th April. The opening match will be held between New Zealand and Srilanka, at the Providence Stadium in Guyana, tonight at 11 pm (BD time). The hosts West Indies and Ireland will face off in the other match of the day at 03 am in the same stadium. Bangladesh Television will telecast all the matches live as well as Star Cricket and Super Sport-2. This years world cup features 12 participants (Australia, Afghanistan, Bangladesh, England, India, Ireland, New Zealand, Pakistan, South Africa, Srilanka, West Indies, Zimbabwe) who will be divided in four groups. In the group A, Bangladesh will be facing Pakistan (1st May) and Australia (5th May). In the first T20 world cup in 2007 at South Africa, India defeated archrivals, Pakistan to clinch the title. Though Pakistan came back to win the trophy by defeating Srilanka in 2009 at England. The next T20 world cup will be held in Srilanka, in 2012
